This paper proposes a new type of OAuth 2.0 token backed by a distributed ledger, which involves security, distributed systems, software engineering, and cryptography. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.Distributed (Distributed Computing), and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
